## Image Organization

### Standard Structure

```
app/assets/images/
├── logo.png              # Main logo
├── logo-dark.png         # Dark mode logo
├── favicon.ico           # Favicon
├── hero-background.jpg   # Hero image
├── default-avatar.png    # Default user avatar
├── icons/                # SVG icons
│   ├── check.svg
│   ├── cross.svg
│   ├── arrow-right.svg
│   └── menu.svg
├── illustrations/        # Larger illustrations
│   ├── empty-state.svg
│   └── error-404.svg
└── social/              # Social media images
    ├── og-image.jpg     # Open Graph
    └── twitter-card.jpg # Twitter Card
```

### Using Images

```erb
<!-- Hero section -->
<section class="relative h-96">
  <%= image_tag "hero-background.jpg", 
      alt: "Hero background",
      class: "absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" %>
  <div class="relative z-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Welcome</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Logo in navigation -->
<nav class="flex items-center">
  <%= link_to root_path do %>
    <%= image_tag "logo.png", alt: "Company Logo", class: "h-8" %>
  <% end %>
</nav>

<!-- Icons -->
<button class="flex items-center gap-2">
  <%= image_tag "icons/check.svg", class: "w-5 h-5" %>
  <span>Confirm</span>
</button>

<!-- Avatar with fallback -->
<%= image_tag user.avatar_url.presence || "default-avatar.png",
    alt: user.name,
    class: "w-10 h-10 rounded-full" %>
```

